Reasoning: The paper discusses cognitive aspects of design, both individual and collective, and focuses on the information processing framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of design problems and the different types of activities involved in design, which could also fit under the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
